Description: Greek classical style female terracotta figure head fragment wearing low polos, veil and draped garments. Mould-made and solid. Traces of white coating preserved, originally painted. Also a white post depositional cocreation covers the broken area. Made of light brown clay with a dark grey core. Only left side of head preserved.
Curator's comments: Found unregistered, but with labels from the EEF stating they were from Petrie's excavations at Naukratis in 1885, however objects from Kamiros were also in this box. 5th century BC parallels of standing or seated women from Rhodes (Higgins 1970, 116-123, 208, 293).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (DB.337) (Phase 3)
